    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="512"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d512">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 738.3915/115.]</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Dominican Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 13.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 24, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 12th instant, wherein you discuss the Dominican-Haitian
                    boundary <pb facs="0474" n="358" xml:id="pg_358"/> question and inform the
                    Department that certain Haitian authorities have committed acts in contravention
                    of the status quo which was agreed by both Governments should be observed
                    pending a definite settlement of the boundary dispute.</p>
                <p>In reply you are informed that the Department will give this matter its prompt
                    and careful consideration and will take such action as the facts may seem to
                    warrant.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
